Therefore, $\zeta'(-2n) = -2 \zeta'(1 + 2n) (-1)^n$

If $\zeta'(-2n) = 0$, then $0 = -2 \zeta'(1 + 2n) (-1)^n$, which implies $\zeta'(1 + 2n) = 0$.

